The SA Revenue Service s (Sars) long-time spokesperson Adrian Lackay has resigned.However, Sars today would not confirm his resignation. We don t comment on the movement of staff, spokesperson Marika Muller said.Lackay would also not comment on the matter saying he was not permitted to speak to the media.The troubled revenue service has seen a number of senior officials resign or be suspended recently, some ending up in the Labour Court.This has been amid allegations of a special projects unit engaging in illegal activities in Sars.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.